TY  - JOUR
T1  - On Monotone Recursive Preferences
AU  - Bommier, Antoine
AU  - Kochov, Asen
AU  - Le Grand, François
Y1  - 2017/09/01
PY  - 2017
DA  - 2017/09/01
DO  - https://doi.org/10.3982/ECTA11898
T2  - Econometrica
JF  - Econometrica
JO  - Econometrica
JA  - Econometrica
SP  - 1433
EP  - 1466
VL  - 85
IS  - 5
KW  - Recursive utility
KW  - monotonicity
KW  - stationarity
PB  - John Wiley & Sons, Ltd
SN  - 0012-9682
UR  - https://doi.org/10.3982/ECTA11898
Y2  - 2024/03/26
N2  - We explore the set of preferences defined over temporal lotteries in an infinite horizon setting. We provide utility representations for all preferences that are both recursive and monotone. Our results indicate that the class of monotone recursive preferences includes Uzawa?Epstein preferences and risk-sensitive preferences, but leaves aside several of the recursive models suggested by Epstein and Zin (1989) and Weil (1990). Our representation result is derived in great generality using Lundberg's (1982, 1985) work on functional equations.
ER  - 

